It's what I tried to do. My setup was that there's this culture that isn't really explained, imagine vikings, picts, that sort of shit.
There's a viking warrior and a female wolf-girl who's referred to as a berserker traveling alone on a pilgrimage in a snowy landscape. There's a lot of tension between the two because he sees her as a murdeorus beast - berserkers have bouts of insanity - and she sees him as a scary warrior dude on the edge who's going to kill her at the drop of a hat. There's genuine fear going on between the two. The idea was that they get closer while they're struggling in the wilderness and eventually while they're spending the night in a cave they get closer to each other in the glowing firelight and have tender missionary sex while holding hands.
I then went out to justify my depravity and began fleshing out all the background things, and I decided that they were both headed to a sacrificial pit at the top of the mountain to appease the evil fairy gods. The mountain is cursed in that the cold slowly erodes your memories as well, so they develop paranoid schizophrenia toward each other, and eventually it's established that people who get to the top of the pit will be so fearful and confused that they'll fight and kill each other. Whoever survives will die in the cold after he leaves, and whoever dies is taken as a sacrifice. They are excited by the fae dwelling in the place to fight. The man sees human skulls on the ground, the girl sees wolf skulls, they understand that one has to die. They fight but as they're crippled from their wounds they have a second of awareness where they remember about the pit, and they hold hands and flee. They are chased by fae all the way to the edge of the forest and when they're out they embrace and die in the snow and worst of all without having sex.
